@startuml componentes
' ======================================================================
' BurgerPOS - Diagrama de Componentes (Entrega 1)
' Vista de despliegue en tiempo de ejecucion sobre Docker Compose
' ======================================================================

title BurgerPOS - Diagrama de Componentes (runtime)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle uml2
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #F8F8F8
  BorderColor #2E6FAC
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #E8F4FD
  BorderColor #2E6FAC
}
skinparam node {
  BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
  BorderColor #555
}
skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor #FFFEF0
  BorderColor #B8860B
}

node "Dispositivo del personal\n(tablet, PC, smartphone)" as Cliente {
  component "Navegador Web" as Browser
}

node "Servidor Linux\n(Ubuntu 22.04 LTS o equivalente)" as Server {
  node "Docker Engine 24+" as Docker {
    component "Contenedor: burgerpos-app" as AppCont {
      component "ASP.NET Core 10\nRuntime" as Runtime
      component "BurgerPOS.Web\n(Razor Pages)" as WebComp
      component "ASP.NET Core\nIdentity" as Identity
      component "Entity Framework\nCore 10" as EF
    }

    database "Contenedor: burgerpos-db\nPostgreSQL 16" as DB {
      component "Volumen\n/var/lib/postgresql/data" as Vol
    }
  }
}

' ============ Comunicacion ============
Browser -down-> WebComp : HTTPS\npuerto 443\n(publicado al host)
WebComp --> Identity : autentica\nusuario
WebComp --> EF : consultas\ny comandos
EF -right-> DB : TCP 5432\n(red interna Docker)
Identity --> EF : repositorio\nde usuarios
DB --> Vol : persiste\ndatos

note right of AppCont
  Imagen Docker construida
  desde el Dockerfile de
  BurgerPOS. Stateless:
  puede reiniciarse sin
  perdida.
end note

note right of DB
  Imagen oficial postgres:16.
  Datos en volumen persistente
  para sobrevivir reinicios y
  recreaciones del contenedor.
end note

note bottom of Docker
  docker-compose.yml define
  ambos contenedores con
  health checks y red privada
  exclusiva para ellos.
end note

@enduml
